AB  - This study utilises recently developed tests based on ranks and signs, in addition to the traditional variance ratio test, to examine the behavior of Euro exchange rates. We show that adjustments for multiple tests must be employed in order to avoid size distortions. Overall, such adjustments provide evidence consistent with random walk behavior of Euro exchange rates.
